  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 28-year-old man presents after falling from a ladder onto concrete. He reports abdominal pain but is alert and oriented. Initial vital signs are BP, 110/70; P, 95. A FAST examination is performed and shows no free fluid. Twenty minutes later, he develops increasing abdominal pain, and repeat vital signs are BP, 95/60; P, 118. What is the most appropriate next step?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Repeat FAST examination"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Administer vasopressors"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Obtain pelvic X-ray"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Obtain CT abdomen and pelvis with IV contrast"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Initiate massive transfusion protocol"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>Correct – <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4N03Yg&anker=Zefeb92d093a9fbf8b7c983722bdbb10d\" data-learningcard-id=\"4N03Yg\" data-anker=\"Zefeb92d093a9fbf8b7c983722bdbb10d\" data-section-id=\"mlcVxc0\" data-sememe-id=\"7h042f\">FAST</a> has limited <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Z252fcd07b99eb21a8bff067bee67fd9d\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Z252fcd07b99eb21a8bff067bee67fd9d\" data-section-id=\"EfW8Lk0\" data-sememe-id=\"wkXhJy\">sensitivity</a> for detecting small amounts of hemorrhage, particularly less than 500 mL, and has a high <span data-sememe-id=\"5BWiYL0\">false-negative rate</span> in hemodynamically stable patients. With clinical deterioration and hemodynamic changes suggesting evolving <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kO0msT&anker=Z6023d435aa502ba29fe59ecc0f2f9df5\" data-learningcard-id=\"kO0msT\" data-anker=\"Z6023d435aa502ba29fe59ecc0f2f9df5\" data-sememe-id=\"-VbDCs\">shock</a>, repeating the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4N03Yg&anker=Zefeb92d093a9fbf8b7c983722bdbb10d\" data-learningcard-id=\"4N03Yg\" data-anker=\"Zefeb92d093a9fbf8b7c983722bdbb10d\" data-section-id=\"mlcVxc0\" data-sememe-id=\"7h042f\">FAST</a> can detect accumulating free fluid that may have been below the detection threshold on the initial examination. </div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kO0msT&anker=Z75813684cbaddcd436339b6b8d787255\" data-learningcard-id=\"kO0msT\" data-anker=\"Z75813684cbaddcd436339b6b8d787255\" data-section-id=\"ZI1ZYR0\" data-sememe-id=\"qNbCX8\">Vasopressors</a> are not indicated in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kO0msT&anker=Ze21245728c8c3ff94b781a6d7209eab4\" data-learningcard-id=\"kO0msT\" data-anker=\"Ze21245728c8c3ff94b781a6d7209eab4\" data-section-id=\"fkckMc0\" data-sememe-id=\"XGc9Bd0\">hemorrhagic shock</a> and may mask the bleeding source while reducing <span data-sememe-id=\"Ef18LT0\">perfusion</span> to vital organs. The patient's hemodynamic changes suggest ongoing blood loss, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kO0msT&anker=Z75813684cbaddcd436339b6b8d787255\" data-learningcard-id=\"kO0msT\" data-anker=\"Z75813684cbaddcd436339b6b8d787255\" data-section-id=\"ZI1ZYR0\" data-sememe-id=\"qNbCX8\">vasopressors</a> would artificially maintain blood pressure while <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=1j02zf&anker=Z92dc7ad213286f5cf282cc52ad7ff5d0\" data-learningcard-id=\"1j02zf\" data-anker=\"Z92dc7ad213286f5cf282cc52ad7ff5d0\" data-section-id=\"apcQLW0\" data-sememe-id=\"7sa4wN\">masking</a> the underlying bleeding source. This could delay recognition of the need for definitive <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Zf2c5e34516e4f09e004b65620d3462a1\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Zf2c5e34516e4f09e004b65620d3462a1\" data-section-id=\"4qX3A_\" data-sememe-id=\"UI1bXR0\">hemorrhage control</a>. </div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>While <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=A60RnS&anker=Z302395fa53b6096eda0d6a50e247fdd4\" data-learningcard-id=\"A60RnS\" data-anker=\"Z302395fa53b6096eda0d6a50e247fdd4\" data-section-id=\"lEcvDV0\" data-sememe-id=\"ZyXZd00\">pelvic</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=in0JGg&anker=Zf22a2d04575027ccbd9bc2a111f58066\" data-learningcard-id=\"in0JGg\" data-anker=\"Zf22a2d04575027ccbd9bc2a111f58066\" data-sememe-id=\"eK0x2S\">X-ray</a> is commonly performed during the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=YI0nYh&anker=Z1ac9cff2c246c57c842ae7e18ff24749\" data-learningcard-id=\"YI0nYh\" data-anker=\"Z1ac9cff2c246c57c842ae7e18ff24749\" data-sememe-id=\"bcYHaL\">primary survey</a> in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4N03Yg&anker=Ze99c35011e3521f2455031319e96fe10\" data-learningcard-id=\"4N03Yg\" data-anker=\"Ze99c35011e3521f2455031319e96fe10\">trauma patients</a>, it would not address the immediate clinical concern for intraabdominal bleeding suggested by the abdominal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> and hemodynamic deterioration. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=A60RnS&anker=Z302395fa53b6096eda0d6a50e247fdd4\" data-learningcard-id=\"A60RnS\" data-anker=\"Z302395fa53b6096eda0d6a50e247fdd4\" data-section-id=\"lEcvDV0\" data-sememe-id=\"ZyXZd00\">Pelvic</a> imaging would be appropriate if there were clinical signs of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=n307Qf&anker=Zb20069dc1365b1c98f6347e135b4e75a\" data-learningcard-id=\"n307Qf\" data-anker=\"Zb20069dc1365b1c98f6347e135b4e75a\" data-section-id=\"ONaIYO\" data-sememe-id=\"9xYNAr\">pelvic instability</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>While CT imaging is more sensitive for detecting intra-abdominal injuries, the patient's hemodynamic changes warrants another step. CT would also require the transport of a potentially unstable patient away from the resuscitation area.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>While <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=2M0TLg&anker=Z6518cb29459c99c0659b02cfa0f2c12d\" data-learningcard-id=\"2M0TLg\" data-anker=\"Z6518cb29459c99c0659b02cfa0f2c12d\" data-section-id=\"qF1CQi0\" data-sememe-id=\"VK1G230\">massive transfusion</a> may be required if <span data-sememe-id=\"ycWdU40\">major bleeding</span> is confirmed, this patient’s current status does not meet activation criteria. The immediate priority is confirming the bleeding source, with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=2M0TLg&anker=Z0d767a500a4efcb1314a93ab2616de44\" data-learningcard-id=\"2M0TLg\" data-anker=\"Z0d767a500a4efcb1314a93ab2616de44\" data-sememe-id=\"jo0_bS\">transfusion</a> coordinated alongside definitive <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Zf2c5e34516e4f09e004b65620d3462a1\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Zf2c5e34516e4f09e004b65620d3462a1\" data-section-id=\"4qX3A_\" data-sememe-id=\"UI1bXR0\">hemorrhage control</a>.</div>",
